{0 day11-lib}

Shared utilities used across day11 libraries and binaries. {!Day11_lib.Run_log}
tracks the lifecycle of a batch run with structured JSONL logging,
phase files for mid-run status checks, and a final summary.
{!Day11_lib.Progress} maintains immutable progress state written as
[progress.json] for web dashboard polling. {!Day11_lib.History} provides
append-only per-package build history in JSONL format with file locking
for concurrent access. {!Day11_lib.Status_index} aggregates all packages' current
build status into a single snapshot, detecting changes between runs.
{!Day11_lib.Notify} sends messages to Slack, Zulip, Telegram, Email, or stdout.
{!Day11_lib.Disk_usage} reports cache disk consumption by category. {!Day11_lib.Gc}
garbage-collects unreferenced build layers and stale odoc store
entries. {!Day11_lib.Classify} scans build logs to categorize failures as
transient, missing depext, or genuine build errors. {!Day11_lib.Epoch} manages
atomic documentation deployment via versioned epoch directories and a
live symlink. {!Day11_lib.Build_config} persists batch run parameters so
rerun/cascade commands need no CLI arguments. {!Day11_lib.Build_lock} tracks
in-progress builds via file locks for dashboard and status reporting.
{!Day11_lib.Package_list} generates the list of successfully-built packages for
publishing.

